repository-code: "https://github.com/hemeda3/aygrep"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - code-search
  - inverted-index
  - sparse-ngrams
  - grep
  - trigram
  - rust
  - ai-agents
abstract: >-
  ayg is an indexed code search tool that uses sparse n-gram inverted indexes
  with frequency-weighted boundaries to search large codebases 1,000x faster
  than ripgrep. Designed for AI coding agents and human developers. The approach
  was reverse-engineered from Cursor's published sparse n-gram technique.
